review_blob: I didnt catch the ginger/cinnamon flavors that others here noted, I expected them to be more notable. Its quite malty, though there are plenty enough hops to balance it out. Its quite smooth, good in cold weather, and overall a great session beer. Too bad its only available three months. $7 for the pack here, well worth it!
Light aroma, barely detectable. Smells lightly of malts. Beautiful clear light-golden tint. Flavor is very light, almost no bitterness. Malts detectable but not great in number. Great carbonation.
Bottled. Head is medium-thin, dissipates quickly (seems common in Mrzen style lagers). Malts dominate aroma. Copper colored. Malt dominates flavor, slight bitter finish. Carbonation is medium-light.

Bottle. Light malty aroma. Head pours medium-thin, dissipates fairly quicky. Color is an amber-copper. Malt flavor dominates, as expected in a Mrzen style. Medium carbonation, very slight bitter finish.

Pours a somewhat murky golden amber color with thin to no head. Smell dominated by hops with hints of vague citrus fruit. Significant level of carbonation. Taste slightly bitter, dominated by hops. Clean and crisp.
Lightly burnt orange color, not much head. Faint bread aroma with hops and light caramel scent. Medium carbonation. Taste is malty, lightly bitter. Dry finish. One of my favorite beers.
Pours dark brown, reddish when held to light. Strong alcoholic smell. Light carbonation, little head. Smooth, faint taste of alcohol. Dominating malt, no hops detectable.
